name: CQ.Log
doc:
A facility to write log messages to the console.
Use the variable window.CQ_initial_log_level to ...

props.name: FATAL
props.doc: <static> Log level for fatal error messages.

props.name: OFF
props.doc: <static> Log level to turn logging off (default).

methods.name: debug
methods.doc:
<static> Writes a message to the console if log level is set to
DEBUG or higher.

methods.name: error
methods.doc:
<static> Writes a message to the console if log level is set to
ERROR or higher.

methods.name: fatal
methods.doc:
<static> Writes a message to the console if log level is set to
FATAL or higher.

methods.name: info
methods.doc:
<static> Writes a message to the console if log level is set to
INFO or higher.

methods.name: setLevel
methods.doc:
<static> Sets the log level.

methods.name: trace
methods.doc:
<static> Writes a message to the console if log level is set to
TRACE or higher.

methods.name: warn
methods.doc:
<static> Writes a message to the console if log level is set to
